  "prompt": "How much do psychologists charge for a cognitive behavioural therapy?",
  "response": "The cost of Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) can vary widely depending on several factors:\n\n1. Location\n- Urban areas tend to be more expensive\n- Different regions have different rates\n\n2. Therapist's experience and credentials\n- More experienced therapists typically charge higher rates\n- Specialists may have higher fees\n\n3. Session duration\n- Typically 45-60 minutes\n- Average cost ranges between $100-$250 per session\n\n4. Insurance coverage\n- Some insurance plans cover part or all of therapy costs\n- Copays can range from $20-$50 per session\n\n5. Type of practice\n- Private practice might be more expensive\n- Community health centers or sliding scale clinics can be more affordable\n\n6. Online vs. in-person therapy\n- Online sessions might be slightly cheaper\n- Telehealth options can range from $60-$200 per session\n\nAverage estimated costs:\n- Without insurance: $150-$250 per session\n- With insurance: $20-$50 copay\n- Sliding scale clinics: $50-$100 per session\n\nThese are general estimates, and actual costs can vary significantly. It's best to contact local therapists or your insurance provider for precise pricing.",
